column5: Hey all.  It's been a while.  Fishing has taken the back seat for me in the last few months but I thought I'd share my trout closer trip from the fall.  It was one of the longer portage trips I've ever taken although I was able to use a dolly.  Hell, I even managed to carry in a Heinekeg.  All things said and done, we had a very successful trip.  Nothing huge, but a very chunky strain of specks was more than willing to bite much of the weekend.  When it wasn't freezing cold we snapped some pics. Enjoy!
Some of those males remind me of male pink salmon. Neat looking fish, and well done on the trip
Man, those fish are prime! Fantastic trip. Congrats.
totally awesome. congrats!
Great bunch of fish and I for one and thrilled to have you back.  Cheers
good to see ya back Doc. Beauty specimens there.
Love the variation in colors
Hey Luc! Good to see you back!  Nice report  TDunn
Welcome back!
Some really nice looking fish!
Beaut Specks Doc  Unfortuanately I have to Hate ya now
Great trip! Nice to have ya back.
Welcome back. Beauty fish.
THE most beautiful freshwater fish!!  Thanks, Doc!!
Some nice specks there for sure, looks like a great trip.
Welcome back. Fitting photos. Thanks for sharing on these cold days.
Beauty brookies right there!!! Welcome back dude.

Doc so happy to see ya back , missed ya . Those are some of the best looking fish I have ever seen .. How can any female fish of any kind NOT want to spawm with them , The one in the first pict the spots etc. just buties ...Specs have to be the best looking fish ...
Beautiful fish in deed. Well the pics match YOUR handle.  Welcome back. Dan O.
A triumphant return at that!  Those are beautifully coloured speckles.
Welcome back dude....colourful fish for a colourful character....nice shooting
Welcome back Doc , great pictures
Welcome back and great report
Awesome little gems Doc !! Well come home dude
